  'Angle Chasing...again', 'Olympiad', 'Long',
  'Resource', 'Problem Set', 'NMTC',
  2026, 'Problem Set 2', 'Problem 1: Angle Chasing...again Note: If you want a real challenge, attempt part (d) while skipping the other parts without reading them. LetABCbe a triangle with circumcircle Γ. LetD̸=Abe the second intersection of the internal bisector of ̸ BACwith Γ. We defineEto be the intersection of lineCDwith the line perpendicular toBCthroughB, andω to be the circumcircle ofADE. The line parallel toADpassing throughE intersectsωatF̸=E. Moreover, let the tangents to Γ atAandCintersect atT. (a) Prove thatDE=DC. (b) Show thatF ADEis an isosceles trapezoid. An isosceles trapezoid consists of two opposite sides parallel and the other two opposite side equal in length. (c) Prove that△F AT ∼= △DCT (d) Show thatF Tis tangent toω.* Page 2 NMTC Problem Set 2 18th February 2026',
