  'Resource', 'Problem Set', 'NMTC',
  2026, 'Problem Set 3', 'Problem 2: Combinatorics 1. Several real numbers are written on the board. At each step, we are allowed to choose two numbersa, bon the board, such thata−b≥2, and replace them witha−1, b+ 1. Prove that we can do only finitely many steps. 2. In a cursed forest, there are 55 wolves, 17 cats, and 6 sparrows. Every time a wolf eats a cat, it becomes a sparrow; every time a wolf eats a sparrow, it becomes a cat; every time a cat eats a sparrow, it becomes a wolf. Finally, at some moment, two species are extinct and animals of only one species remain. When this happens, at most how many animals can there be in the forest? Page 3 NMTC Problem Set 3 21th February 2026',
