(
  'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5-part-ii-23', 'published', 'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5', 'Physics',
  23, '23', 'Physics',
  'Physics MCQ', 'Subject MCQ', 'MCQ',
  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'The graph on the right shows the velocity of a race car moving along a straight line as a function of time. What is the magnitude of the displacement of the car from t = 2.0 seconds to t = 4.0 seconds?',
  '["20 m","40 m","60 m","80 m"]'::jsonb, 2, 'We know: Displacement = Area of Velocity time graph Area Total = 1 2 b h = 1 2 (4) (40) = 80 m Find the area from t=2s to t=4s Area = Area Total −Area from 0 to 2s Area from 0 to 2s = 1 2 (2) (20) = 20 m Thus, Area = 80 −20 = 60 m',
  4, '/api/storage/paper-assets/physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5/figures/q23-p4-manual.webp', '{}'::jsonb
),
(
  'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5-part-ii-24', 'published', 'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5', 'Physics',
  24, '24', 'Physics',
  'Physics MCQ', 'Subject MCQ', 'MCQ',
  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'An archer uses a bow to fire two similar arrows with the same string force. One a rrow is fired at an angle of 60° with the horizontal, and the other is fired at an angle of 45° with the horizontal. Compared to the arrow fired at 60°, the arrow fired at 45° has a',
  '["longer flight time and longer horizontal range","longer flight time and shorter horizontal range","shorter flight time and longer horizontal range","shorter flight time and shorter horizontal range"]'::jsonb, 2, 'We know, Range = v2sin(2θ) g Time of Flight = 2vsin(θ) g For 60◦: Range = v2 g sin(2 · 60) Time of Flight = 2v g sin(60) = v2 g ( √ 2 ) m = 2v g ( √ 2 ) s For 45◦: Range = v2 g sin(2 · 45) Time of Flight = 2v g sin(45) = v2 g (1) m = 2v g ( 1 √ 2) s comparing in a calculator we get: Range of 45◦> Range of 60◦ Time of 45◦< Time of 60◦',
  null, '', '{}'::jsonb
),
(
  'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5-part-ii-25', 'published', 'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5', 'Physics',
  25, '25', 'Physics',
  'Physics MCQ', 'Subject MCQ', 'MCQ',
  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'Which is an acceptable unit for impulse?',
  '["N•m","J•s","J/s","kg•m/s"]'::jsonb, 3, '⃗J = Z t2 t1 ⃗F(t) dt = (kg · m/s2) · (s) = kg ·m/s',
  null, '', '{}'::jsonb
),
(
  'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5-part-ii-26', 'published', 'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5', 'Physics',
  26, '26', 'Physics',
  'Physics MCQ', 'Subject MCQ', 'MCQ',
  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'During a collision, an 84-kilogram driver of a car moving at 24 meters per second is brought to rest by an inflating air bag in 1.2 seconds. The magnitude of the force exerted on the driver by the air bag is approximately.',
  '["7.0 x 10^1 N","8.2 x 10^2 N","1.7 x 10^3 N","2.0 x 10^3 N"]'::jsonb, 2, '⃗F = ∆⃗p ∆t = (mvf −mvi) tf −ti = (84 · 0 −84 · 24) 1.2 = −1.68 × 103N ⃗F ≈1.7×103N',
  null, '', '{}'::jsonb
),
(
  'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5-part-ii-27', 'published', 'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5', 'Physics',
  27, '27', 'Physics',
  'Physics MCQ', 'Subject MCQ', 'MCQ',
  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'A block weighing 15 newtons is pulled to the top of an incline that is 0.20 meter above the ground, as shown on the right. If 4.0 joules of work are needed to pull the block the full length of the incline, how much work is done against friction?',
  '["1.0 J","2.0 J","3.0 J","7.0 J"]'::jsonb, 0, 'To find work against friction: Work Total = Work by Friction + Work against Gravity Work Friction = Work Total −Work against Gravity = 4.0J −mgh = 4.0J −(15)(0.20) = 1.0 Joule',
  5, '', '{}'::jsonb
),
(
  'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5-part-ii-28', 'published', 'physics-2022-final-physics-2022-b4137e5', 'Physics',
  28, '28', 'Physics',
  'Physics MCQ', 'Subject MCQ', 'MCQ',
  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
