  30, '30', 'Physics',
  'Physics MCQ', 'Subject MCQ', 'MCQ',
  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'A catapult with a spring constant of 1.0 x 10^4 newtons per meter is required to launch an airplane from the deck of an aircraft carrier. The plane is released when it has been displaced 0.50 meter from its equilibrium position by the catapult. The energy acquired by the airplane from the catapult during takeoff is approximately',
  '["1.3 x 10^3 J","2.0 x 10^4 J","2.5 x 10^3 J","1.0 x 10^4 J"]'::jsonb, 0, 'The energy acquired by the airplane is the same as the energy stored in the spring: U = 1 2kx2 where k = 1.0 × 104 N/m and x = 0.5m. Thus, U = 1 2(1.0 × 104)(0.50)2 = 1.25 × 103 ≈1.3 × 103J',
  5, '', '{}'::jsonb
),
