  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'A 2.0 x 10^6 hertz radio signal is sent a distance of 7.3 x 10^10 meters from Earth to a spaceship orbiting Mars. Approximately how much time does it take the radio signal to travel from Earth to the spaceship?',
  '["4.11×10–3 s","2.43 x 10^2 s","2.19 x 10^8 s","1.46 x 10^17 s"]'::jsonb, 1, 'We know, S = v × t (7.3 × 1010) = (c) × t t = 7.3 × 1010 3 × 108 t = 2.43 × 102s',
