  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'In which situation is the net force on the object equal to zero?',
  '["a satellite moving at constant speed around Earth in a circular orbit","a bicycle moving at constant speed on a straight, level road","an automobile braking to a stop","a pitched baseball being hit by a bat"]'::jsonb, 1, 'Velocity = |⃗v| ˆv Fnet = 0 anet = 0 In option A: The magnitude of velocity (speed) remains constant but centripetal acceleration causes the unit vector (direction) of velocity to change and thus net force is not zero. In option B: The magnitude of velocity (speed) and direction remains constant. Thus no net force.',
