  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2022, 'NSTC 2022 Physics Paper', 'The speed of light in vacuum, 𝑐, depends on two fundamental constants, the permeability of free space, 𝜇0, and the permittivity of free space, 𝜀0. The speed of light is given by 𝑐 = 1 √𝜇0𝜀0 . The units of 𝜀0 are N-1.C2.m-2. The units for 𝜇0 are',
  '["kg-1m-1C2","kg.m.C-2","kg.m.s-4.C-2","kg-1s-3C-2"]'::jsonb, 1, 'Solving: c = √ϵ0µ0 c2 = µ0ϵ0 (m/s)2 × (N−1 · C2 · m−2) = 1 µ0 µ0 = (m/s)2 × (N−1 · C2 · m−2) = (m · s−1)2 × ((kg · ms−2)−1 · C2 · m−2) = (m · s−1)−2 × (kg · ms−2)+1 · C−2 · m2 = kg · m · C−2',
  8, '', '{}'::jsonb
),
